113573 28/10/2015 香港 Maxpark Enterprises Ltd 收购 China Fortune Investments (Holding) Ltd 香港 Private investor(s) 啤酒、葡萄酒和酒类专营店 (4453); 体育用品、游艺器材及娱乐用品、乐器专卖店 (4511) 32.26 (官方数据) 100 Chinese jewelries retailer China Fortune Investments disclosed it will acquire Hong Kong's wine and golf products distributor Maxpark Enterprises for HKD 250mn (USD 32.3mn). The sellers in the deal are private investors Li, Pan Xiao Dong, Moo Chii Yuan, Liu Yuon-Chan and Bo Zhou. The buyer will pay in cash and convertible notes. Completion of the deal is subject to certain conditions precedent. The acquisition is in line with buyer's strategy to diversify its portfolio of businesses. Maxpark Enterprises has five subsidiaries which are engaged in trading of wine products, cigars, as well as golf products in Hong Kong. China Fortune Investments is engaged in retail sale of diamond, gemstone and other jewelries in China, and provision of information technology services and solutions to Chinese hospitals and medical institutions. 113570 28/10/2015 中国 Xin Wing Enterprises Ltd 收购 Youyuan International Holdings Ltd; Cathay Capital Group 中国; 美国 　 建材、园艺设备供应商 (444) 124.64 (官方数据) 61 Chinese wrapping tissue paper manufacturer Youyuan International and U.S.-based Cathay Capital Group agreed to acquire a combined 61% stake in Chinese wallpaper provider Xin Wing Enterprises for RMB 793mn (USD 124.6mn), Youyuan International reported. The deal will be implemented as a cash contribution to the target's capital. Upon completion of the deal, Youyuan International will hold a 41% stake in the target, while Cathay Capital Group will own a 20% stake. The current sole owner of Xin Wing Enterprises is Ms. Ke Jinzhen, will retain a 39% stake in the target company. Ms. Ke Jinzhen is the daughter of Mr. Ke Wentuo, the Chairman, executive director and controlling shareholder of Youyuan International. Completion of the deal is subject to customary closing conditions. The acquisition is in line with the strategy of Youyuan International to enhance its market position in the paper industry value chain. Xin Wing Enterprises and its subsidiaries, produce and distribute high quality wall paper backing paper. Youyuan International is a Hong Kong-listed manufacturer of double-sided and single-sided machine finished wrapping tissue paper, copy paper, paper towels and ivory boards.

The target companies are named Fuzhou Huaguan Knitting and Sprining, and Fuzhou Huasheng Textile. The seller acts in the deal, via its subsidiary Right Lane International Limited. Completion of the deal is subject to customary closing conditions. Art Textile Technology International Co Ltd will inject the proceeds from the disposal, into its property operating business. Fuzhou Huaguan Knitting and Sprining focuses on dyeing process of grey fabrics, while Fuzhou Huasheng Textile engages in trial weaving of grey fabrics.

112742 28/10/2015 土耳其 Millenicom Telekomunikasyon Hizmetleri 收购 EWE AG 德国 European Telecommunication Holding 固定电信服务 (5171) 　 　 100 EWE Turkey Holding, the local unit of German energy group EWE AG, announced the acquisition of Turkish alternative telecom services provider Millenicom Telekomunikasyon Hizmetleri from Germany-based European Telecommunication Holding. The transaction is subject to approval by the Turkish competition regulator. No financial details were disclosed. Millenicom has licenses to provide fixed-line telephony service, Internet service, infrastructure operation service and mobile virtual network operator (MVNO) service. The company was established in 2004 by European Telecommunication Holding, which is a market leader in the German ethnic telecommunications market. EWE is active in energy, telecommunications and information technology and is one of the largest utility companies in Germany with more than 9,000 employees and annual sales of over EUR 8bn. The sellers are Brazilian computer repairing services provider Braxis Tecnologia de Informacao SA and local holding company Serpartners Participacoes e Administracao SA. After the acquisition, Cap Gemini SA reached a majority stake in Capgemini Brazil. Capgemini Brazil, headquartered in Sao Paulo city (Sao Paulo state, Brazil), provides administrative and financial services. It also owns the Gaspar Facility (municipality of Gaspar, Santa Catarina state, Brazil) that provides finance and accounting services. Cap Gemini provides consulting, technology and outsourcing services. The company develops software and offers information systems and project management, and education and training services. Cap Gemini offers its services to financial services providers and to the petroleum, automotive, aerospace and telecommunications industries in Europe, the United States, Asia, and South Africa. Cap Gemini registered a turnover of USD 10.57bn in 2014. _________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________ A provedora francesa de consultoria, tecnologia e serviços de terceirização Cap Gemini SA adquiriu uma participação de 3.6% na sua subsidiária brasileira Capgemini Business Services Brazil (Capgemini Brazil) por USD 78.93 mn (USD 20.19mn), o assessor financeiro da Capgemini Brazil revelou para o DealWatch. As vendedoras são a provedora brasileira de serviços de reparação de computadores Braxis Tecnologia de Informação SA e a local holding Serpartners Participações e Administração SA. Após a aquisição, a Cap Gemini SA alcançou uma participação majoritária na Capgemini Brasil. A Capgemini Brasil, sediada em São Paulo (SP, Brasil), prove serviços administrativos e financeiros. A empresa também administra a facilidade Sonda Procwork em Gaspar (município de Gaspar, SC, Brasil), que fornece serviços de finanças e contabilidade. A Cap Gemini oferece serviços de consultoria, tecnologia e terceirização. A empresa desenvolve software e oferece administração de sistemas informáticas e projetos, e serviços de educação e formação. A Cap Gemini prove os seus serviços a prestadores de serviços financeiros e para as indústrias petrolífera, automotiva, aeroespacial e de telecomunicações na Europa, Estados Unidos, Ásia e África do Sul. Cap Gemini registou um faturamento de USD 10.57bn em 2014.

112625 28/10/2015 匈牙利 Parisi Nagyaruhaz commercial property in Budapest 收购 Hungarian Development Bank (MFB) 匈牙利 Orco Property Group SA 房地产 (531) 　 　 100 Hungarian state-owned development bank MFB Zrt. has acquired historical commercial building Párisi Nagyáruház in Budapest from Luxembourg-registered real estate company Orco Property Group, the Hungary Around the Clock reported. The value of the transaction was kept confidential by the two parties. The transaction was carried out through newly-established subsidiary MFB Real Estate (MFBI), wholly-owned by MFB Zrt. Following the deal, MFBI will continue to operate and utilize the building in compliance with existing functions and valid tenancy contracts. MFBI does not plan further acquisitions in the real estate market. According to the government press office, the Hungarian state had exercised its pre-emptive right to buy the property and the transaction was completed on 09 June 2015. Párisi Nagyáruház (Paris Grand Department Store) was built in 1882 as the country's first modern department store. The property was rebuilt in 2011 following a devastating fire. In 2005, Orco Property Group acquired the building and refurbished it with an investment of EUR 17.0mn. Its tenants include Alexandra retail book store, the internet firm Ustream, while the building's famous Lotz Hall is home to a cafe shop. Founded in 1991, Orco Property Group is an investor, developer and asset manager in the Central European real estate and hospitality market. The company focuses mainly on Germany, the Czech Republic, Hungary, Poland, Croatia and Slovakia. Its shares are listed on the Paris Stock Exchange and the Warsaw Stock Exchange. In 2014, the company had total assets under management of EUR 374.0mn.

MabSpace Biosciences Co Ltd focuses on the discovery and development of IP-protected therapeutic antibodies for the treatment of cancer, metabolic disorders, chronic kidney diseases, and autoimmune diseases. Founded on 2008, Lily Asia Ventures specialises in investments in growth stage and various stages of development from start-up to commercialization.

112496 28/10/2015 巴西 Santa Vitoria Acucar E Alcool Ltda 收购 The Dow Chemical Co 美国 Mitsui & Co Ltd 基础化学原料制造 (3251) 200 (官方数据) 50 Japanese trading company Mitsui & Co Ltd announced it has agreed to sell its entire shareholding (50%) in Brazilian chemicals producer Santa Vitoria Acucar e Alcool Ltda (SVAA) to U.S. chemicals manufacturer The Dow Chemical Co for approximately BRL 780.43mn (USD 200mn). The transaction is part of Mitsui's BRL 19.5bn (USD 5bn) Euro Medium Term Note Programme. Upon the transaction being terminated, Mitsui expects to maintain and strengthen its strategic partnership and alliance with Dow. The deal is subject to regulatory approvals and is expected to close by 12 July 2016. SVAA, headquartered in the municipality of Santa Vitoria (Minas Gerais state, Brazil), produces and distributes bio-ethylene, bio-polyethylene and sugarcane derived chemicals. The company was founded in 2011 as a 50/50 joint venture between Mitsui and Dow Quimica SA, a subsidiary of Dow. It operates around 36,000 hectares of plantation and an industrial park, having a processing capacity of 2.7 million tons of sugarcane and a productive capacity of up to 240 million litres of ethanol per harvest. Dow Chemical, established in 1897, is an international manufacturer and supplier of chemical products. The company provides more than 5,000 products within four segments: specialty chemicals, advanced materials, agrosciences and plastics, and operates 188 manufacturing plants in 36 countries, engaging 52,700 employees. Dow Chemical is listed on the New York Stock Exchange, and posted USD 58bn in revenues and USD 69bn in net assets in 2014. Mitsui & Co Ltd, established in 1947, is a global diversified trading company with interests in the energy, machinery and infrastructure, metals, chemicals, food, textile, logistics, and finance sectors. The company operates a network of 150 offices in 67 countries worldwide, and engages more than 44,800 employees. Mitsui has gas distribution business in Brazil that consists of regional monopolies based on the concessions granted by state governments. ________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________ A trading japonesa Mitsui & Co Ltd anunciou que entrou em um acordo para a venda da totalidade da sua participação (50%) na fabricante brasileira de produtos químicos Santa Vitória Açúcar e Álcool Ltda (SVAA) para a fabricante norte-americana de produtos químicos Dow Chemical Co, por cerca de BRL 780.43mn (USD 200mn). A transação faz parte do Programa EMTN (Euro Medium Term Note Programme) da Mitsui com um orçamento de BRL 19.5bn (USD 5bn). Após o fechamento da transação, a Mitsui espera manter e reforçar a sua parceria e a sua aliança estratégica com a Dow. O acordo está sujeito a aprovações regulamentares e se espera que seja fechado até 12 de Julho de 2016. A SVAA, sediada no município de Santa Vitória (MG, Brasil), produz e distribui bio-etileno, polietileno e bio-produtos químicos derivados da cana-de-açúcar. A empresa foi constituída em 2011 como uma parceria com participações iguais entre a Mitsui e Dow Química SA, uma subsidiária da Dow. A empresa opera cerca de 36,000 hectares de plantação e um parque industrial, com uma capacidade de processamento de 2.7 milhões de toneladas de cana-de-açúcar e uma capacidade produtiva de até 240 milhões de litros de etanol por safra. A Dow Chemical, fundada em 1897, é uma fabricante e fornecedora internacional de produtos químicos. A empresa oferece mais de 5,000 produtos em quatro segmentos: produtos químicos especiais, materiais avançados, ciências agrícolas e plásticos e opera 188 fábricas em 36 países, envolvendo 52,700 colaboradores. A Dow Chemical está listada na Bolsa de Valores de Nova York, e apresentou um faturamento de USD 58bn e um ativo total líquido de USD 69bn em 2014. A Mitsui & Co Ltd, fundada em 1947, é uma empresa de comércio global diversificada, com interesses nos sectores da energia, máquinas e setores de infra-estrutura, metais, produtos químicos, alimentos, têxtil, logística e finanças. A empresa opera uma rede de 150 escritórios em 67 países em todo o mundo, e envolve mais de 44,800 funcionários. Mitsui tem negócio de distribuição de gás no Brasil, representado por monopólios regionais com base nas concessões outorgadas pelo governo do estado.

Hallstar, founded in 1986 and headquartered in Chicago (Illinois state, U.S.), manufactures polymer additives and personal care ingredients. 112511 28/10/2015 洪都拉斯 Los Prados 53 MW solar project in Honduras 收购 Scatec Solar ASA; Norfund 挪威 　 太阳能发电 (221114) 　 　 100 Norwegian integrated independent solar power company Scatec Solar ASA announced it has acquired, together with compatriot private equity and venture capital firm Norfund, the Los Prados 53 MW solar project located in Honduras. Financial terms were not disclosed. Raymond Carlsen, CEO of Scatec Solar, said that with this acquisition the company further strengthens its position in the Honduran and Latin American solar market. Scatec Solar added that it will build, own and operate the power plant. The deal value is BRL 1.1bn (USD 284.6mn), American daily newspaper The New York Times reported. Under the agreement, BRL 400mn (USD 103mn) will be paid after the completion of the transaction, BRL 450mn (USD 116mn) - in annual instalments starting from 2018 to 2022, and BRL 225mn (USD 60mn) - if certain business goals get accomplished. According to Mr. Fernando Pinto, Carlyle's managing director responsible for the transaction, Grupo Uniasselvi is a strategic asset with important competitive advantages. Mr. Fernando Borges, co-head of Carlyle in Brazil, said that the acquisition aligns with Carlyle's growth strategy in the country, due to the fact that Grupo Uniasselvi offers essential services to Brazilians. He added that the partnership with Vinci would also be beneficial for the company. The New York Times informed that the deal comes as a result of the prolonged Brazilian recession and the underperforming educational system. In addition, Brazilian Antitrust Authority CADE required Kroton to sell Uniasselvi so as to approve its merger with Brazilian educational group Anhanguera Educacional. Uniasselvi, founded in 1997, is a university complex that provides both distance learning and on-campus education. The university has around 100,000 students enrolled in undergraduate and graduate programs. It operates 48 centres across several Brazilian states and seven campuses in the state of Santa Catarina. The company operates offices in Rio de Janeiro, em Sao Paulo e Nova York and employs around 30,000 professionals. The Carlyle Group is a global alternative investment firm with USD 193bn in assets under management across 128 funds and 159 fund of funds vehicles as of 30 June 2015. The Carlyle Group is listed on the NASDAQ Stock Market and had a turnover of USD 1.16bn and a net profit of USD 915mn for 2014. Kroton Educacional SA, established in 1966, is a private education group, focused on primary, secondary and post-secondary education segments with strong presence in the states of Mato Grosso, Minas Gerais, Bahia, Santa Catarina and Parana. With a team of 8,000 professionals, the company operates a network of 53 higher education units in 83 cities in 18 Brazilian states, and 447 distance learning graduation centres, serving nearly 700,000 students. In addition, SeverGroup and TUI AG will contribute new investments in the capital of TUI Russia & CIS in line with the new participation ratios. Respectively, SeverGroup will invest USD 17mn and additionally provide a short-term financing of USD 5.1mn, ITAR-TASS news agency reported. TUI AG will contribute a new equity investment of USD 3mn. Some payables by the JV to TUI AG will be deferred in order to provide a short-term funding of up to USD 4.9mn for the winter season 2015/2016. TUI Russia & CIS was created in April 2009 on the basis of Russian companies VKO Group, Mostravel and Ukrainian Voyage Kiev. The company operates over 500 tour agencies under the TUI brand, including agencies under franchise agreements. TUI Russia & CIS provides more than 20 kinds of tourism services and has over 600,000 clients annually. Alexey Mordashov is the main shareholder and CEO of Russian metal, energy and mining conglomerate Severstal. Mordashov owns approximately 13% in TUI AG.

Under the deal, Mustang will get an 80% stake in Australi8an firm Montepuez Minerals, giving it an effective 64% interest in Licence 4143L, 56% interest in Licence 4258L and 56% interest in Licence 5030L. A total of USD 150,000 of the sum is payable in cash and the remainder in shares. Licences 4143L, 4258L and 5030L cover an area of 15,800 ha and are located close to reportedly the world's single largest ruby deposit held by Gemfields. In the year ended 30 June 2015, Gemfields recovered 8.4 million carats of ruby and corundum at an average grade for the year of 26 ct/tonne, mining at a rock handling cash cost of USD 6.16 per tonne. Mustang Resources focuses on diamond and graphite exploration and mining in Mozambique and its portfolio includes the Save River diamonds project and the Balama graphite project. Pontomobi, founded in 2007, provides an integrated portfolio of mobile marketing tools and advertising services, including SMS, MMS, voice and Bluetooth marketing, mobile websites, mobile applications, and mobile advertising. The company operates offices in Sao Paulo, Belo Horizonte, Recife, Rio de Janeiro and London, and has some 120 employees. Dentsu Aegis Network is part of Japanese advertising group Dentsu Inc and provides brand, media and digital communications services including digital creative execution, content creation, media planning, among others. It operates in 123 countries worldwide and employs 27,000 people. RBS, founded in 1957, is a multimedia communications holding company, comprising 21 broadcast TV stations, 25 radio stations, eight newspapers and four internet portals. The company also engages in education, marketing, book publishing, logistics and media graphics business in the states of Rio Grande do Sul and Santa Catarina. ______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: Em 19 de novembro de 2015 o assessor jurídico da Pontomobi revelou para o DealWatch que o valor do negócio era de BRL 80mn (USD 21.1mn). ORIGINAL: A empresa britânica de mídia e comunicação de marketing digital Dentsu Aegis Network assinou um contrato para adquirir a totalidade do capital social da companhia brasileira de mobile marketing e publicidade Pontomobi Tecnologia Informática Ltda (Grupo.Mobi), por um valor não revelado, a empresa-alvo anunciou. Os vendedores são o grupo brasileiro de comunicação multimídia Grupo RBS Ltda (60%), agindo através do seu fundo de capital de risco E.Bricks, e certos investidores não revelados (40%). Nos termos do acordo, a Pontomobi vai passar a se chamar Pontomobi Linked by Isobar. A Pontomobi, fundada em 2007 pelo empresário brasileiro Leonardo Xavier, oferece um portfólio integrado de ferramentas de mobile marketing e serviços de publicidade, incluindo SMS, MMS, voz e Bluetooth marketing, sites móveis, aplicativos móveis e mobile advertising. A empresa opera cinco escritórios em São Paulo, Belo Horizonte, Recife, Rio de Janeiro e Londres, e tem cerca de 120 colaboradores. A Dentsu Aegis Network faz parte do grupo publicitário japonês Dentsu Inc e fornece serviços digitais, de marca e de comunicação incluindo execução digital criativa, criação de conteúdo, planejamento de mídia, entre outros. 111870 11/10/2015 英国 Gas fields in the North Sea 收购 INEOS Group Ltd 瑞士 LetterOne Group 石油和天然气的开采 (211) 750 (市场估计) 100 UPDATE: The acquisition was completed, both INEOS and DEA Deutsche Erdoel AG (through which LetterOne Group acted as seller) announced in separate press statements. ORIGINAL: Swiss chemicals major INEOS Group Ltd said it agreed to acquire several gas fields in the North Sea from LetterOne Group, the energy assets vehicle set up by Russian investment holding company Alfa Group Consortium. The deal value was not disclosed. According to banking sources, as cited by Reuters, the assets were valued at about USD 750mn, LetterOne initially expected to receive some USD 1-1.2bn for the gas fields. The transaction is pending approval from the European Commission and is expected to close later in 2015. In March 2014, LetterOne agreed to acquire the gas licences in question (around 40) as a part of a EUR 4.5bn (USD 6.3bn) acquisition of RWE Dea, the Hamburg-based oil and gas unit of German indebted utility group RWE AG. The deal was closed in March 2015 but the British authorities refused to approve it and gave LetterOne six months to dispose of the UK assets, threatening to revoke the licences. The UK government was worried that the gas supplies from the respective fields in the North Sea could be blocked in case of future sanctions against Russia. As reported, the acquired assets will contribute to INEOS' European energy and feedstock strategy as the company is one of the major operators of chemical plants and a large consumer of hydrocarbons. The assets will be operated by the new INEOS Upstream business division to be seated in London. The U.K. North Sea gas fields reportedly provide up to 8% of the gas in the U.K. The largest of them, Breagh and Clipper South, are located close to existing INEOS' sites in the North East and Scotland. INEOS is a global manufacturer of petrochemicals, speciality chemicals and oil products. Its network spans 65 sites in 16 countries throughout the world. The group's annual turnover is USD 54bn. INEOS earlier voiced an intention to be the leading UK player in onshore gas development. The company also holds several shale gas licences in England and Scotland and is set to invest USD 1bn in a project to supply U.S. shale gas to the UK and Norway. The owners of Alfa Group Consortium, Mikhail Fridman and German Khan, founded LetterOne Group in 2013 with the purpose to invest part of the capital they obtained from the sale of their ownership in TNK-BP, the Russian arm of British oil major BP.

LukOil claims to be the second largest non-state publicly traded oil company worldwide by proven reserves of hydrocarbons. The group holds 0.8% of global oil reserves and 2.1% of global oil production.

O Sr. William John Evans Jr., vai deter os restantes 30% do capital social da TAS e permanecerá no cargo de Diretor Presidente da TAS. A TAS é um prestador de serviços aeroportuários nos EUA, sediada em Phoenix (Arizona). O seu portfólio oferece serviços aeroportuários de ground-handling de aeronaves, armazenagem de carga, operação de terminal, entre outros serviços. A empresa está presente em sete aeroportos americanos: ORD - Chicago O'Hare International Airport, LAX - Los Angeles International Airport, SFO - San Francisco International Airport, ATL - Atlanta Hartsfield International Airport, EWR - Newark Liberty International Airport, HSV - Huntsville International Airport and BDL - Bradley International Airport. A CCR é a holding, que faz parte do Grupo CCR, uma das maiores companhias de concessão de infraestrutura do mundo, com uma rede de 3,265 quilômetros de rodovias e valor de mercado de BRL 20bn (USD 5.17bn) (a data de 8 de outubro de 2015). Erste Bank said that it has written off all these arrears in 2014 and their sale to the Czech fund represents an one-off income for the bank. Erste Bank is one of the first banks in Serbia to sell corporate non-performing loans to a foreign fund, and it plans to sell another portfolio of NPLs by the end of the year. Erste Bank a.d. Novi Sad, former Novosadska Banka, is the 12th largest bank in terms of total assets in Serbia, with a market share of 3.5%. Established in 1864, the bank is the oldest financial institution in the country. Currently it operates a network of 73 retail branches, as well as 10 corporate centres and employs nearly 1,000 people. As of 30 June 2015, it reported total assets of RSD 103.11bn (USD 963.5mn). Based in Prague, APS Holding is a distressed asset investment management and servicing company, focused across Central and South Eastern Europe. It has additional offices in 8 other CEE countries and employs around 350 people. The company was founded in 2004 by private equity firm Slavia Capital. In April 214 the International Finance Corporation (IFC) signed an agreement with APS Holding under which the two sides will take over bad loans in Bulgaria, Montenegro, Romania, Serbia and other Eastern and Southeast European countries.

ORIGINAL: German road and rail transportation services provider Eurogate Intermodal GmbH (Eurogate) has agreed to acquire a 16% stake in Brazilian counterpart Contrail Logistica SA (Contrail) for an undisclosed sum, Brazilian on-line journal Valor Economico reported. Under the agreement, Eurogate has the option to purchase another 16% stake in Contrail until 2018. Contrail started operations in 2014 and has already consumed BRL 100mn (USD 24mn) of the budget that is estimated at BRL 1.1bn (USD 264mn). According to Thomas Eckelmann, president of Eurogate, Contrail has a great potential for future growth and expansion in terms of containers transported via railway to Santos port (Sao Paulo state, Brazil). The investment is based on a plan composed by three main strategic points: the first is the operational Cubatao intermodal terminal (Sao Paulo state), called TIPS; the second one is the rallying fleet of "double track" wagons that will have a 150% increased capacity and 14 operational trains until 2021; the third one is the construction of seven new rail-road terminals in the Sao Paulo state until 2016. Contrail was founded in 2008 in Sao Paulo city (Sao Paulo state, Brazil) and provides railway and road transportation services. It has an area of 300,000 m2 and an installed annual capacity for 1.2 million tonnes of teus (twenty-foot equivalent unit). Eurogate was founded in 1999 in Hamburg (Germany) and provides customised road and rail transport services in Europe. It offers conveyance services, operates a system of container unit trains traveling from Bremerhaven and Hamburg as well as inland terminals in Munich, Nuremberg, Regensburg, Ulm, among other German cities.
